definition.value: An azaspiro compound having a monofluoro-substituted chromane skeleton spiro-linked to an imidazolidinedione ring.

An N-{4-[2-ethyl-1-(1H-1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butyl]phenyl}-1,3-benzothiazol-2-amine that is the (R)-enantiomer of talarozole. The racemate is used for the treatment of keratinization disorders, psoriasis and acne.
